Police have launched a murder investigation after a father of three was shot dead, after confronting two robbers as he closed his business for the night.

Pragaret Singh, 35, was shot in the chest and abdomen as he left Manchester Food Traders in Openshaw, Greater Manchester, just after 6pm on Friday.

Detectives said Mr Singh, known to friends as Charlie, was believed to have grappled with at least one of the men.

