Armed police who attended the scene found Mr Singh lying in the road. He was taken to Manchester Royal Infirmary but pronounced dead at 7.30pm.

Mr Singh, who had children aged two, five and seven, had run the wholesale food firm on the Manchester industrial estate for more than 15 years.

The victim’s brother, known as Tiggy, said Mr Singh ‘worked 24 hours a day’ to provide for his wife Sukhwinder and children.

‘He was robbed of his life. He was happy, jolly and full of life – he never said anything bad about anyone.

‘He was the kind of person who’d go out of his way to help anyone in need. They could have shot him in the leg, they could have hit him with a stick – but instead they shot him twice.

‘He’s the kind who probably would have put up a fight. He was fit and full of life.’

