Police described one of the attackers as black, in his 20s or 30s, with spiky knotted hair, clean shaven, tall slim build and wearing a jacket with the sleeves rolled up.

They are appealing for information about the movements of a small silver car, possibly a Vauxhall, which may have been used by the thieves.

Detective Superintendent Jon Chadwick, of Greater Manchester Police, said: ‘His family are absolutely and utterly distraught and our thoughts are with them.

‘We believe this is the tragic death of an innocent businessman and father of three simply trying to protect his livelihood from criminals.

‘As a result, Charlie’s entire family have suffered an unimaginable loss.’

Police said the robbers made off with a ‘large amount of money’.

Anyone with information should call police on 101 or Crimestoppers, anonymously, on 0800 555 111.

